               <p>THOMAS JOHNSON. I live in <placeName id="t18220522-112-crimeloc595">White Lion-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220522-112-crimeloc595" type="placeName" value="White Lion-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220522-112-crimeloc595" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220522-112-off593 t18220522-112-crimeloc595"></join>, and am a <rs id="t18220522-112-viclabel596" type="occupation">lapidary</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220522-112-victim1046 t18220522-112-viclabel596"></join>. The prisoner was in my service; he left on the 1st of April, and on the 9th of May I missed the mill; I had not seen it for four months - I found it in his room; he said it was mine, and he took it for a pattern.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. He had been your apprentice - A. Yes, and lived eight years with me. My son and him quarrelled, which caused him to leave, and he set up for himself,</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220522-112-person1047">
